    "minides": "Twin-turbo V6, quattro AWD, and five doors — the RS5 Sportback is the everyday performance car done right.",
    "description": "The Audi RS5 Sportback (B9.5 facelift) is sold in India as a CBU import, priced at ₹1.07 Crore (ex-showroom). It is powered by a 2.9-litre biturbo V6 TFSI producing 444 bhp at 5,700 rpm and 600 Nm from 1,900–5,000 rpm, paired with an 8-speed tiptronic automatic and Audi's quattro permanent all-wheel drive. The RS5 Sportback sprints from 0–100 km/h in 3.9 seconds and is electronically limited to 250 km/h (280 km/h with the RS Dynamic package). Features include Matrix LED headlamps with dynamic indicators, a 12.3-inch Audi Virtual Cockpit Plus, a 10.1-inch MMI touch display, Bang & Olufsen 3D sound system, RS sport suspension, six airbags, and a frameless door design. The RS5 Sportback competes with the BMW M4 Competition Gran Coupe and Mercedes-AMG C 43 in India."
  },
